oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Alexander's swinging bridge
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a swinging bridge over the White Oak River. Two unidentified people can be seen standing on the bridge in the distance. Ernest Vernon Alexander (1863-1956) installed the bridge to get to the home he built and named Sunnyside. Handwriting at the top and bottom of the photo reads: "Swinging Bridge - Rugby Tenn." and "Near our house." Text at the bottom of the photo reads: "Alexander's Swinging Bridge, Rugby, Tenn."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Trees; Bridges; People
